What You Need
1. Tech Stack

Python 3.9+ — core language
Data libraries: pandas, numpy
Visualization: matplotlib, seaborn, plotly
ML/DL models: scikit-learn, tensorflow/keras or pytorch
Stock data: yfinance (Yahoo Finance API — free)
Optional: ta-lib or pandas-ta for technical indicators

2. Data Sources

yfinance — historical OHLCV data (Open, High, Low, Close, Volume)
Alpha Vantage / Quandl — alternative APIs (need API key)
News/Sentiment (optional advanced step) — Twitter API, NewsAPI



 PROJECT WORKFLOW



Phase 1: Data Collection
    └── Fetch historical stock data (yfinance)
    └── Choose ticker(s): AAPL, TSLA, NIFTY50, etc.

Phase 2: Data Preprocessing
    └── Handle missing values
    └── Feature engineering (Moving Averages, RSI, MACD, Bollinger Bands)
    └── Normalization / Scaling (MinMaxScaler)

Phase 3: Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
    └── Plot price trends
    └── Correlation heatmaps
    └── Volume analysis

Phase 4: Model Building
    └── Baseline: Linear Regression
    └── Intermediate: Random Forest, XGBoost
    └── Advanced: LSTM (Long Short-Term Memory) — best for time series

Phase 5: Training & Evaluation
    └── Train/test split (80/20 or walk-forward validation)
    └── Metrics: RMSE, MAE, MAPE, R²

Phase 6: Prediction & Visualization
    └── Plot predicted vs actual prices
    └── Future N-day price forecast

Phase 7: (Optional) Dashboard
    └── Streamlit or Flask web app
    └── Interactive charts with Plotly


Suggested Starting Point


Which stock(s)? (e.g., Apple/AAPL, Indian NIFTY50, crypto like BTC) - 
Scope? Simple price prediction, or full dashboard?
Model preference? Beginner (Linear Regression) → Advanced (LSTM)
